{"parse":{"title":"Indian History Congress","pageid":19827780,"revid":841636719,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Indian History Congress</b> is the largest professional and academic body of Indian historians with over 10,000 members. It was established in 1935.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The name of any new applicant for membership needs to be proposed and seconded by existing Ordinary or Life Members.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Awards\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Awards</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Indian_History_Congress&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The lead to establish all India national congress of historians was taken by Poona historians during the colonial rule. The first session took place in <a href=\"/wiki/Bharat_Itihas_Sanshodhak_Mandal\" title=\"Bharat Itihas Sanshodhak Mandal\">Bharat Itihas Sanshodhak Mandal</a>, Pune in 1935.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Major historians like <a href=\"/wiki/Datto_Vaman_Potdar\" title=\"Datto Vaman Potdar\">Datto Vaman Potdar</a>, Surendra Nath Sen (who later became the first director of <a href=\"/wiki/National_Archives_of_India\" title=\"National Archives of India\">National Archives of India</a>), Sir Shafaat Ahmad Khan attended the first session.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Historians <a href=\"/wiki/Mohammad_Habib\" title=\"Mohammad Habib\">Mohammad Habib</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Susobhan_Sarkar\" title=\"Susobhan Sarkar\">Susobhan Sarkar</a> and later <a href=\"/wiki/Nurul_Hasan\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Nurul Hasan\">Nurul Hasan</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Ram_Sharan_Sharma\" title=\"Ram Sharan Sharma\">Ram Sharan Sharma</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Satish_Chandra\" title=\"Satish Chandra\">Satish Chandra</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Bipan_Chandra\" title=\"Bipan Chandra\">Bipan Chandra</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Romila_Thapar\" title=\"Romila Thapar\">Romila Thapar</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Irfan_Habib\" title=\"Irfan Habib\">Irfan Habib</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/M._Athar_Ali\" title=\"M. Athar Ali\">Athar Ali</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Barun_De\" title=\"Barun De\">Barun De</a>, Iqtidar Alam Khan, <a href=\"/wiki/B._N._Mukherjee\" title=\"B. N. Mukherjee\">B. N. Mukherjee</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/K_N_Panikkar\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"K N Panikkar\">K N Panikkar</a>, Brajadulal Chattopadhayay, <a href=\"/wiki/Dwijendra_Narayan_Jha\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dwijendra Narayan Jha\">Dwijendra Narayan Jha</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Sumit_Sarkar\" title=\"Sumit Sarkar\">Sumit Sarkar</a>, Sabyasachi Bhattacharya and <a href=\"/wiki/Pritam_Saini\" title=\"Pritam Saini\">Pritam Saini</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>  have had a long association with the Indian History Congress.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Zee_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Zee-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> Its current President is <a href=\"/wiki/R._Champakalakshmi\" title=\"R. Champakalakshmi\">R. Champakalakshmi</a> of <a href=\"/wiki/Jawaharlal_Nehru_University\" title=\"Jawaharlal Nehru University\">Jawaharlal Nehru University</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Zee_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Zee-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Veteran <a href=\"/wiki/Marxist\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Marxist\">Marxist</a> leader <a href=\"/wiki/Jyoti_Basu\" title=\"Jyoti Basu\">Jyoti Basu</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> was invited to speak the 61st session at Kolkata.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Awards\">Awards</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Indian_History_Congress&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Awards\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Indian History Congress has constituted <a href=\"/wiki/Vishwanath_Kashinath_Rajwade\" title=\"Vishwanath Kashinath Rajwade\">Vishwanath Kashinath Rajwade</a> Award for lifelong service and contribution to Indian history which was given to professor <a href=\"/wiki/Ram_Sharan_Sharma\" title=\"Ram Sharan Sharma\">R.S. Sharma</a> in 2002.<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Indian_History_Congre